noupdate changes
-----------------

- Halts update check obsolete timer
- Default settings have update checking set to never
- Icons changed slightly to denote the build you're running (a stale colour, heh)

Supported systems
-----------------

FileZilla-noupdate has been tested specifically (although not extensively) with the following:
- Windows 10
- Windows 11
- Debian 10 (Buster)
- Debian 11 (Bullseye)

The following are also presumed to work:
- Windows 8.1 
- Major Linux distributions
- FreeBSD and other BSD variants
- Mac OS X

Tested architectures:
- x86-64 / amd64

FileZilla may be able to run on additional systems and architectures.



Overview
--------

FileZilla Client is a free, open source FTP, FTPS and SFTP client.

This program is free software; you can redistribute it and/or modify
it under the terms of the GNU General Public License as published by
the Free Software Foundation; either version 2 of the License, or
(at your option) any later version.

Features
--------

- Supports FTP, FTP over SSL/TLS (FTPS) and SSH File Transfer Protocol (SFTP)
- Cross-platform
- IPv6 support
- Available in many languages
- Supports resume and transfer of large files >4GB
- Easy to use Site Manager and transfer queue
- Bookmarks
- Drag & drop support
- Speed limits
- Filename filters
- Directory comparison
- Network configuration wizard
- Remote file editing
- Keep-alive
- HTTP/1.1, SOCKS5 and FTP Proxy support
- Logging to file
- Synchronized directory browsing
- Remote file search
- Tabbed interface to connect to multiple servers


